Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. FIT one piecrust into a 9-inch tart pan; trim edges evenly to top of tart pan. Line pastry with aluminum foil, and fill with pie weights or dried beans. Bake 10 minutes; remove weights and foil. Bake 5 additional minutes or until crust is golden. Cool on a wire rack. Combine 1/2 cup SPLENDA(R) Granulated Sweetener, cornstarch, salt, milk, and eggs in a heavy saucepan; whisk until mixture is smooth. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to low and cook for 1 minute or until mixture thickens. Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy; gradually add hot custard mixture to cream cheese, beating until blended. Stir in vanilla. Spoon filling mixture into prepared tart shell. Press plastic wrap directly over surface of pie; cool completely. Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in a small saucepan; stir and let stand 1 minute. Stir in SPLENDA(R) Granulated Sweetener and lemon juice; bring mixture to a boil over medium heat stirring until gelatin dissolves. Cool mixture to room temperature. Arrange berries over tart; drizzle berries with glaze; chill 1 hour.